{"word":"προσμολεῖν","slug":"προσμολεῖν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσμολεῖν</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <a href='S:aorist tense'>aor.</a> of <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> <el>προσβλώσκω</el> which does not occur.\n<p/><i>to come</i> or <i>to go, reach, arrive at</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to approach</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}